The paper discusses a reinforcement learning algorithm, specifically Q-learning, and its sample complexity in Markov Decision Processes (MDPs). This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also deals with Lipschitz continuous functions, which is a topic in optimization and analysis (cs.DS). The use of MDPs and decision making also relates to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the analysis of regret in the algorithm falls under the category of mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
